modules.description: This module represents files with associated names and content, providing operations to construct file values from strings, file paths, or input channels. It supports delayed reading of file content via channels, useful for handling large or dynamically generated data. Concrete use cases include preparing source code files for submission to the MOSS plagiarism detection service.

This module facilitates the submission of code files for plagiarism analysis by converting them into a format suitable for the MOSS service. It supports multiple programming languages and configurable submission options such as user ID, experimental mode, and base files. The core functionality works with file representations that can be constructed from strings, file paths, or input channels, enabling efficient handling of large or dynamically generated source data. For example, it allows checking student assignments for code similarity or verifying originality in version-controlled repositories by preparing and submitting structured file content.
